# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __bool__, __str__, __repr__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# decimal.Decimal: __bool__ = true (bool(Decimal('0')) is False, bool(Decimal('1'))
# is True), __str__ = true (str(Decimal('3.14')) returns '3.14'),
# __repr__ = true (repr(Decimal('3.14')) returns "Decimal('3.14')").
# This true/true/true pattern is the key finding of wave 674 for the decimal
# module: Decimal fully implements bool, string, and repr conversion protocols.
# All other decimal classes (Context, DecimalException, InvalidOperation,
# Overflow, Underflow): false for all three operators.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

